Figure 8
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="80" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="80">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="80">
<taxonomicName class="Sordariomycetes" genus="Dendrostoma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Dendrostoma parasiticum" order="Diaporthales" pageId="13" pageNumber="80" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="parasiticum">Dendrostoma parasiticum</taxonomicName>
is distinguished from 
<taxonomicName genus="D." lsidName="D. quercus" pageId="13" pageNumber="80" rank="species" species="quercus">D. quercus</taxonomicName>
by its shorter and narrower conidia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
