<geoCoordinate direction="north" orientation="latitude" precision="15" value="33.6575">33°39'27&quot;N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate direction="east" orientation="longitude" precision="15" value="109.120834">109°07'15&quot;E</geoCoordinate>
, 2504 m a.s.l., on branches of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Quercus wutaishanica" order="Fagales" pageId="13" pageNumber="80" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="wutaishanica">Quercus wutaishanica</taxonomicName>
, 8 Jul. 2017, N. Jiang (holotype: BJFC-S1570; ex-type culture: CFCC 52762).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="80" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="80">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="80">Parasiticum, referring to the fungus causing canker diseases on different hosts.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="80" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="80">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="80">
Sexual morph not observed. Asexual morph: Conidiomata pycnidial, conical to spherical, occurring separately, yellow, semi-immersed in bark, 350-600 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
high, 1000-1800 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
diam.; wall of several layers of bright yellow textura angularis; central column beneath the disc conical, bright yellow. Conidiophores reduced to conidiogenous cells. Conidiogenous cells lining the inner walls of the cavity, hyaline, smooth, subcylindrical to ampulliform, 7-12 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2-3.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
. Conidia hyaline, aseptate, smooth, multiguttulate, thin-walled, fusoid, straight, (9.2
<normalizedToken originalValue="–)9.3–11.7(–">-)9.3-11.7(-</normalizedToken>
13.6) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
(2.7
<normalizedToken originalValue="–)2.8–3.3(–">-)2.8-3.3(-</normalizedToken>
3.6) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
, l/w = (2.7
<normalizedToken originalValue="–)3–3.9(–">-)3-3.9(-</normalizedToken>
4.2) (n = 50).
</paragraph>
